Hi all,

I'm new to OLPC.  The wiki states:

http://wiki.laptop.org/go/Getting_started_programming

  Sugar's own GUI interface is coded in a GTK derived library (Hippo),
  using an internal "sugar.graphics" package. This package is
  currently in flux and you should not likely start new projects using
  it until the API stabilises. In the meantime please use GTK or
  PyGame (SDL) for you project's GUI.

I think the plan for the organization I'm working with is to use
PyGame for a few activities anyway, but when are the Sugar APIs
expected to stablize?

thanks
